'''Marine Corps Planning Process''' is the primary planning process used by the [[United States Marine Corps]] at all levels.  Its successful execution is widely regarded as essential for mission success. This planning process involves six steps: Problem Framing, Course of Action (COA) Development, COA [[Wargaming]], COA Comparison and Decision, Orders Development, and Transition.<ref>https://www.marines.mil/Portals/59/Publications/MCWP%205-10%20FRMLY%20MCWP%205-1.pdf?ver=2017-08-28-140131-227</ref>

