Active sites include the following:<ref name="parliamentreport"/>
* [[Zimmerwald]] ([[Canton of Berne]]) {{coord|46|53|12.46|N|7|28|41.41|E}} * [[Heimenschwand]] (part of the municipality of [[Buchholterberg]], Canton of Berne) {{coord|46|49|52.81|N|7|42|57.99|E}}: 3 antennas.<ref>[[Military of Switzerland|Swiss Federal Department of Defense]], ''[http://www.admin.ch/cp/f/423981c6_1@fwsrvh.html Deux nouvelles antennes pour l'installation militaire de Heimenschwand]''. 17 March 2005 Press release {{fr icon}}</ref> * [[Leuk]] ([[Canton of Valais]]) {{coord|46|19|05|N|7|38|43|E|region:CH_type:landmark_source:dewiki}}: 4 antennas.<ref>[[Military of Switzerland|Swiss Federal Department of Defense]], ''[http://www.admin.ch/cp/f/435ccb67_3@fwsrvg.html Deux nouvelles antennes sur le site du DDPS de Loèche]''. 24 October 2005 Press release {{fr icon}}</ref>
==Intercepted black sites fax== {{main|Black site#The Onyx-intercepted fax}} On 8 January 2006, the Swiss newspaper ''[[Sonntagsblick]]'' (Sunday edition of the ''[[Blick]]'' newspaper) published a secret report produced by the Swiss government using data intercepted by Onyx.<ref>SonntagsBlick, [http://www.blick.ch/sonntagsblick/aktuell/artikel30413 CIA-Skandal US-Folter-Camps: Der Beweis!] {{de icon}} Accessed on 9 January 2006.</ref><ref name="militarytribunal">[http://www.vbs.admin.ch/internet/vbs/fr/home/documentation/oa009.parsys.0034.downloadList.00341.DownloadFile.tmp/urteilmg6062ciafaxaffaereanonymisiert.pdf Decision of the military tribunal] of 17 April 2007 {{de icon}}. Includes the original article from the Sonntagsblick with the copy of the fax.</ref> The report described a fax sent by the Egyptian department of Foreign Affairs to the Egyptian Embassy in London, and described the existence of [[black site|secret detention facilities]] ("black sites") run by the [[Central Intelligence Agency|CIA]] in [[Eastern Europe]].<ref>[[Swissinfo]], [http://www.swissinfo.org/eng/swissinfo.html?siteSect=106&sid=6367478&cKey=1136749505000 Swiss may have known about secret CIA prisons]. Accessed on 9 January 2006</ref> The Swiss government did not officially confirm the existence of the report, but started a military judiciary procedure for leakage of secret documents against the newspaper on 9 January 2006. While the authenticity of the fax was implicitly confirmed during the trial, the reporter and newspaper were cleared of all charges on 17 April 2007.<ref name="militarytribunal"/><ref>[[Swissinfo]], [http://swissinfo.org/eng/search/detail/Reporters_cleared_of_revealing_military_secret.html?siteSect=881&sid=7725767&cKey=1176838959000 Reporters cleared of revealing military secret]. 17 April 2007</ref>
